t the mechanisms that maintain gender inequality, despite thriving feminist and other equal rights movements, she contributes a fresh vision of how the welfare state developed in the early 20th century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFeminism. 0aWiveszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311119675640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447355854423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447355854/original  a978-3-11-119675-6  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles